24/05/2011
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- The tripartite presidency has started informal consultations on nominees for the new state-level prime minister, Srna news agency reported on Monday (May 23rd).
Boris Buha, adviser to the Serb Presidency member Nebojsa Radmanovic, said now that the BiH lower house has been constituted, the presidency has 15 days to propose a prime minister-designate.
He or she would come from the largest party in FBiH, the Social Democratic Party, or from the main Croat party, HDZ BiH.
The Croat parties insist on the post, saying it should be subject to a rotation principle as well.
(Srna, RTRS - 23/05/11)
